CONNOLLY v. CITY OF NEW YORK. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 11, 1909.) Action by Ellen Connolly against the City of New York.

With this case has been consolidated in this court cases bearing titles as follows: Jas. C. Deering v. City of New York; Gerolamo Danneo v. Same; Frank Danneo v. Same; Herman Fromme v. Same; Henry W. Seabold v. Same.

No opinions. Motions granted, with $10 costs. Orders filed. See, also, 107 N. Y., Supp. 934.
